,'From the Modern Librarys new set of beautifully repackaged hardcover classics by William Faulkneralso available are Snopes, As I Lay Dying, The Sound and the Fury, Light in August, and Absalom, Absalom William Faulkner was a master of the short story. Most of the pieces in this collection are drawn from the greatest period in his writing life, the fifteen or so years beginning in 1929, when he published The Sound and the Fury. They explore many of the themes found in the novels and feature characters of smalltown Mississippi life that are uniquely Faulkners. In A Rose for Emily, the first of his stories to appear in a national magazine, a straightforward, neighborly narrator relates a tale of love, betrayal, and murder. The vicious family of the Snopes trilogy turns up in Barn Burning, about a sons response to the activities of his arsonist father. And Jason and Caddy Compson, two other inhabitants of Faulkners mythical Yoknapatawpha County, are witnesses to the terrorizing of a pregnant black laundress in That Evening Sun. These and the other stories gathered here attest to the fact that Faulkner is, as Ralph Ellison so aptly noted, the greatest artist the South has produced. Including these stories Barn Burning Two Soldiers A Rose for Emily Dry September That Evening Sun Red Leaves Lo Turnabout Honor There Was a Queen Mountain Victory Beyond Race at Morning',1993,4.09,320,1001,14.83,'action_adventure'),(3846,9780679428954,'The Complete Collected Poems of Maya Angelou','Poems 19651992','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=B6283eMxBFgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Presents a definitive collection of poetry from Angelous previous anthologiesJust Give Me a Cool Drink of Water, Oh Pray my Wings Gonna Fit Me Well, And Still I Rise, I Shall Not Be Moved, On the Pulse of Morning, and Shaker, Why Dont You Sing 50,000 first printing.',1994,4.42,273,7701,41.1,'action_adventure'),(3848,9780679431367,'The Sword of Honour Trilogy',NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=kSQCAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Book Jacket Status Jacketed This trilogy of novels about World War II, largely based on his own experiences as an army officer, is the crowning achievement of Evelyn Waughs career. Its central character is Guy Crouchback, head of an ancient but decayed Catholic family, who at first discovers new purpose in the challenge to defend Christian values against Nazi barbarism, but then gradually finds the complexities and cruelties of war too much for him. Yet, though often somber, the Sword of Honour trilogy is also a brilliant comedy, peopled by the fantastic figures so familiar from Waughs early satires. The deepest pleasures these novels afford come from observing a great satiric writer employ his gifts with extraordinary subtlety, delicacy, and human feeling, for purposes that are ultimately anything but satiric.',1994,4.24,711,1068,88.07,'science_fiction'),(3850,9780679434047,'In the Kitchen with Rosie','Oprahs Favorite Recipes','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=GR41sSVe84gC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','With 50 recipes and 8 pages of fullcolor photographs by Micheal McLaughlin.',1994,3.03,142,752,43.39,'horror'),(3851,9780679444596,'Rabbit Angstrom','A Tetralogy','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ajoz5zL4HVgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Four novels trace the life of Harry Rabbit Angstrom against the changing American society from the sixties to the eighties',1995,4.26,1520,1492,34.39,'thriller'),(3855,9780679601128,'Stars in Their Courses','The Gettysburg Campaign JuneJuly 1863','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vLza8sd4PXUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Recreates the Battle of Gettysburg from both the Confederate and Union perspectives',1994,4.45,304,1407,18.83,'fantasy'),(3856,9780679601326,'The Poetry and Short Stories of Dorothy Parker',NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=lcplQ