oman. The sophisticated dalliance among the four serves to obscure an underlying violence, which, when the curtain of civilization is drawn aside, reveals in her fellow guests a very contemporary, perhaps even new, form of insanity. Like many of Durass novels, Destroy, She Said owes much to cinema, displaying a skillful interplay of dialogue and description. There are recurring moods and motifs from the Duras repertoire eroticism, lassitude, stifled desire, a beautiful woman, a mysterious forest, a desolate provincial hotel. Included in this volume is an indepth interview with Duras by Jacques Rivette and Jean Narboni.',1986,3.68,133,532,29.97,'thriller'),(4866,9780802136831,'The Six Wives of Henry VIII',NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9zYYi1v8tnIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Profiles the oftmarried English monarch and the women that came to define him through marriage, detailing their littleknown histories and personalities. Reprint.',2000,4.11,643,53977,12.32,'action_adventure'),(4867,9780802151803,'Sexus','The Rosy Crucifixion I','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=jzjwvQAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','The first novel of Millers frank, autobiographical trilogy uses dream, fantasy, and burlesque to portray the life of a struggling writer in preWorld War I New York',1987,4.04,506,7024,51.67,'fantasy'),(4868,9780802151827,'Tropic of Capricorn',NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=oK7U5DbFA3gC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Banned in America for almost thirty years because of its explicit sexual content, this companion volume to Millers Tropic of Cancer chronicles his life in 1920s New York City. Famous for its frank portrayal of life in Brooklyns ethnic neighborhoods and Millers outrageous sexual exploits, The Tropic of Capricorn is now considered a cornerstone of modern literature.',1961,3.82,348,13549,31.4,'horror'),(4871,9780802449245,'Little Pilgrims Progress','From 