tings of Zen Master Dogen','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=af-BZb7n9P8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Eihei Dogen 12001253, among the first to transmit Zen Buddhism from China to Japan and founder of the important Soto School, was not only a profoundly influential and provocative Zen philosopher but also one of the most stimulating figures in Japanese letters. Kazuaki Tanahashi, collaborating with several other Zen authorities, has produced sensitive and accurate translations of Dogens most important texts. Moon in a Dewdrop contains the key essays of the great master, as well as extensive background materials that will help Western readers to approach this significant work. There is also a selection of Dogens poetry, most of which has not appeared in English translation before. Dogens thought runs counter to conventional logic, employing paradoxical language and startling imagery. It illuminates such fundamental concerns as the nature of time, existence, life, death, the self, and what is beyond self.',1985,4.29,368,946,80.63,'fantasy'),(5286,9780865476066,'Suburban Nation','The Rise of Sprawl and the Decline of the American Dream','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=UZ0-0X4aiwQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Three members of the Founders of the Congress for the New Urbanism give voice to a growing movement in North America to put an end to suburban sprawl and to replace the automobilebased settlement patterns of the past fifty years with a return to traditional planning principles. Reprint.',2001,4.08,320,1898,51.68,'fantasy'),(5287,9780867196207,'Rent Girl',NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=xI_9wAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','The story of a young lesbians advetures in and out of the sex industry on both the East and West Coasts of America.',2004,3.79,239,2401,96.48,'horror'),(5288,9780870610639,'Summa Theologica','Complete 5Volume Set','http://books.google.com/books/co